In order to configure DNS template settings in Plesk, first login to your Plesk administrative panel as admin and do the following steps:

1) select **Settings** from the **Home** page, then click on **DNS Template Settings**.

2) There are a number of different tools here. You can **Switch Off** the local DNS service for all newly created domains, **Add a DNS Record** to the template, and edit the **SOA Records Template**. You can also revert the DNS Template to the default settings, as it was originally when Plesk was first set up.

3) For adding DNS record, click on **Add a DNS Record** and enter the **Record Type**( Here CNAME record), **Domain name** and **Canonical name** details and then click on **OK**.
